Text.Value: What was your connection to the Guild?
Why did they want you to put explosives in the toys?
What secret were you hiding?
You donated explosive toys to the refugees - why?
Leave.
Banites... said to... put explosives... in the toys... or else...
Who killed you?
Where were you getting these explosives from?
His people... I... warned you...
I'm just... an artisan... they... made me... do it...
Why did you hate those refugees so much?
To prove... Steel Watchers... are needed...
None... just... hired... their local thugs...
Who do you mean by 'they'?
What's in this basement?
Fireworks shop... Lower City... password is... 'I'm here to visit... Uncle Felogyr...'
The basement... the toys...
Arfur... a toymaker...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Who are you?
The toys... are there...
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
They might... find... the basement...
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*

Synopsis: Speak with dead dialog for Arfur the toymaker, who worked for Orin to place explosive toys to the refugee donations.
